meanings: me (direct object of a verb, accusative case)
me (direct object of a verb, accusative case)
(accusative) oneself (clitic form of reflexive pronoun sebe)
(dative) to oneself (clitic form of reflexive pronoun sobě)

one's own; belonging to the subject, of the subject, or related to the subject; reflexive possessive pronoun; thus rendered as possessive pronouns including my, your, his, her, our, their, depending on the subject.
(possessive) your, yours, thy, thine (2nd-person familiar, singular only)
(possessive) your, yours (2nd-person singular formal or 2nd-person plural)
